      </div>
    </div>

    <p>Every audit closes with a prioritised action plan, each recommendation ranked by estimated impact and implementation effort.</p>
    </div>

    <div class="reveal">
    <h2>Why Guildford Businesses Need an SEO Audit</h2>

    <p>Guildford sits at the intersection of technology, education, and high-value professional services, and the commercial stakes are considerable. A solicitor on <strong>Guildford High Street</strong> converting one additional client per month from organic search could generate tens of thousands in annual revenue. A property agency covering the borough, where average house prices exceed £600,000, needs every listing page indexed and ranking, as the <a href="/case-studies/guildford-property-firm-local-seo/">Guildford property firm case study</a> sets out in detail. A technology company on <strong>Surrey Research Park</strong> targeting enterprise buyers cannot afford to lose visibility to a competitor with faster, better-structured pages.</p>

    <p>Without an audit, you are navigating by intuition rather than instrument, and in a market this competitive, intuition is not enough. These are the patterns I encounter repeatedly with Guildford businesses:</p>

    <ul>
      <li>Websites where 30 to 60 per cent of pages are not indexed by Google, despite appearing entirely normal to visitors.</li>
      <li>Sites passing desktop speed tests but failing mobile Core Web Vitals, where Google actually measures performance.</li>
      <li>Local businesses with inconsistent Name, Address, Phone (NAP) data across directories, which suppresses local pack visibility.</li>
      <li>Content that targets keywords with negligible local search volume while ignoring terms that Guildford residents actually search.</li>
      <li>Technical problems introduced by CMS updates, plugin conflicts, or hosting changes that went undetected for months.</li>
    </ul>

    <p>An audit replaces guesswork with evidence. You receive a factual assessment of your current position and a ranked list of what to fix first, a roadmap drawn from data, not hunches.</p>
    </div>

    <div class="reveal">
    <h2>Technical Audit Components</h2>

    <p>The technical audit examines your website's infrastructure, the foundation that determines whether search engines can access and understand your content. My <a href="/technical-seo-guildford/">technical SEO service</a> covers implementation, but the audit identifies every issue as a necessary first step.</p>

    <h3>Crawlability and Indexation</h3>

    <p>I crawl your entire site and compare discovered pages against Google Search Console's index coverage report. This reveals pages Google cannot find (orphaned content), pages Google finds but declines to index (quality threshold failures), and pages Google indexes that you would prefer it did not (index bloat from tag pages, parameters, or thin content).</p>

    <h3>Site Speed and Core Web Vitals</h3>

    <p>I test every page template against Google's Core Web Vitals thresholds: Largest Contentful Paint under 2.5 seconds, Interaction to Next Paint under 200 milliseconds, and Cumulative Layout Shift under 0.1. I use both lab data (controlled testing) and field data (real user measurements from Chrome User Experience Report) because they frequently tell different stories.</p>

    <h3>URL Architecture and Internal Linking</h3>

    <p>I map your site's URL structure, internal link graph, and crawl depth. Pages buried more than three clicks from the homepage receive less crawl priority and less link equity, and I identify orphaned pages, redirect chains, broken links, and cannibalisation where multiple pages compete for the same keyword.</p>

    <h3>Structured Data Validation</h3>

    <p>I audit every schema markup implementation on your site. Incorrect structured data can result in manual actions from Google, while missing structured data means missed opportunities for rich results. I validate syntax, check for required properties, and identify schema types relevant to your business that have not yet been implemented.</p>

    <h3>Security and HTTPS</h3>

    <p>I verify HTTPS implementation, check for mixed content, audit security headers, and confirm that HTTP-to-HTTPS redirects are clean, with no chains and no loops. For businesses handling sensitive data, particularly those near <strong>Royal Surrey Hospital</strong> or in financial services along the High Street, security configuration carries additional ranking weight.</p>
    </div>

    <div class="reveal">
    <h2>Content Audit Components</h2>

    <p>Technical infrastructure ensures your pages are crawled and indexed; content quality determines where they rank. The content audit evaluates every page against Google's quality standards and your competitors' content.</p>

    <h3>Thin and Duplicate Content Analysis</h3>

    <p>I identify pages with insufficient unique content (under 300 words with no supporting media), near-duplicate pages that cannibalise one another's rankings, and boilerplate-heavy pages where template content outweighs unique content. Each finding includes a specific recommendation: consolidate, expand, noindex, or remove.</p>

    <h3>Keyword Targeting and Search Intent</h3>

    <p>I analyse which keywords each page currently targets (based on title tags, headings, and content), compare these against actual search queries driving impressions in Google Search Console, and identify misalignments where your content does not match what searchers expect. I also identify keyword gaps, valuable searches your competitors rank for but you do not.</p>

    <h3>Content Depth and Topical Authority</h3>

    <p>Google rewards sites that demonstrate comprehensive coverage of their subject area. I assess your topical authority by mapping your content against the full semantic field of your target topics, and gaps in coverage indicate missed ranking opportunities and reduced authority signals.</p>

    <h3>Title Tags and Meta Descriptions</h3>

    <p>I audit every title tag for length (under 60 characters to avoid truncation), keyword placement, click-through rate potential, and uniqueness. Duplicate or generic titles suppress CTR and waste ranking positions. Meta descriptions are reviewed for compelling, measured copy that encourages clicks from search results.</p>
    </div>

    <div class="not-prose my-12 border-y border-border py-6 flex flex-wrap items-center justify-between gap-4">
      <p class="text-brand font-heading text-lg m-0">See exactly where your site stands.</p>
      <a href="/free-seo-audit-guildford/" class="cta-button">Get your free audit</a>
