    <h2>How Surrey Businesses Use My Audits</h2>

    <p>Different businesses employ audit findings in different ways, depending on their internal resources and strategic goals.</p>

    <p><strong>Professional services firms</strong> on Guildford High Street typically commission the audit and then engage me to implement the recommendations on a monthly retainer. Their sites are sufficiently compact that a focused three-month engagement addresses all critical and high-priority issues.</p>

    <p><strong>Technology companies on Surrey Research Park</strong> often have internal development teams and use the audit as a technical specification document, implementing fixes within their own sprint cycles. I provide ongoing consultation to review their implementation and answer technical questions as they arise.</p>

    <p><strong>E-commerce and property sites</strong> with thousands of pages use the audit to prioritise which site sections to address first. Full implementation may take six to twelve months, so the prioritisation framework ensures the highest-impact changes happen earliest.</p>

    <p><strong>Businesses recovering from ranking declines</strong> use the audit diagnostically. Following a Google Core Update or sudden traffic loss, the audit identifies whether the cause is technical, content-related, or competitive, and prescribes the appropriate recovery strategy.</p>
    </div>

